ugh all of them - the book''s permanent captive soul, you presume.  In a few, it gets the upper hand - turning you into a detachable horsecock to wear on his own body; creating a cheerleader of you, making you re-enact the big game; sending you armed with only a whip to defeat a castle full of vampires.  Though, more often than not, both of you are victims - to power-mad kitsunes, to a legion of fembots, to an army of rampaging bimbos. Though finally, exhausted, your rival ceases toying with you, and releases you from the book; grateful to return to your own familiar form, you nevertheless feel extremely unsteady from the experience; likely an easy target for real-life changes ...', NULL, NULL, N'You open your copy of Practical Transformations and the Metaphysical Realm, eager to ensnare another passing mage.  Sure enough, just as the book demon promised, they are sucked inside, being tormented just like your original captive, in a bewildering variety of adult situations.  In at least a few, it seems to be your initial captive getting the upper hand - turning his temporary guest into a detachable horsecock to wear on one page; creating a cheerleader of his guest on another, making her re-enact the big game; sending her armed with only a whip to defeat a castle full of vampire in a third.  Though in just as many, your two guests are both victims - to power-mad kitsunes, to a legion of fembots, to an army of rampaging bimbos.  Finally, exhausted, your latest victim emerges from the pages of the book, after having taken on dozens of different forms; you have no doubt that the morphic resonance will remain, making them easy targets for further changes in real life.', NULL, NULL, CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2