ver flicker of light guides your eyes. The secluded atmosphere alone would warrant a short dip inside this hidden treasure, but unlike the other hot springs around you, this one is fueled by a small stream that springs from the stone covered lower part of the escarpment itself. The very essence of mana radiates from every drop, and you wonder where its true origin lies. But alas, for now you have nothing but this small paradise for yourself and might as well take a bath. You turn towards the inner wall, where the border between two layers of stone makes a small crevice for potential items or clothes. As you start to soak in the water and feel the mana being absorbed into your body, you consider drinking it. Actually, you nearly feel compelled to, but you shake those thoughts from your head. It has a high concentration of mana inside, which is good for a physical recovery, but you don''t want to turn into a mana sprite or water elemental after drinking it, right? When you are done, you stand up and dry yourself. Although you can''t shake the feeling that the spring left you with more than just an increased mana intake.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 10, 5, 0, 0, 0)
