nto loved ones and that places twist themselves into familiar homes. You have no idea what just happened, but you are apparently encaged in your own memories, fused to the reality you have been thrown into as of late. Though would it be better to accept the dream or to fend of the cruel reality behind it?', NULL, NULL, NULL, N'Some people in this town are scared, some people are hurt and others are lost. Those you can heal. Yet there are also those that lost themselves to the town''s influence, hunting those people still with their own and turning them away from all those that made them a community. This man is one of them and while you can''t seem to find it in your heart to hurt him in return, you wish for him to find himself once again. Gently you reach out to his mind and rifle it for any deep feelings you share, lost below memories of late. As your magic pulls the memories forth from their shallow grave, he stops his actions and seems puzzled. But once he realizes what you have done to him, he will have a hard time to decide if he ever wants to escape it. Confronted with his old self, can he still look his lost ones in the eye or is his true self long gone?', N'Some people in this town are scared, some people are hurt and others are lost. Those you can heal. Yet there are also those that lost themselves to the town''s influence, hunting those people still with their own and turning them away from all those that made them a community. This woman is one of them and while you can''t seem to find it in your heart to hurt her in return, you wish for her to find herself once again. Gently you reach out to her mind and rifle it for any deep feelings you share, lost below memories of late. As your magic pulls the memories forth from their shallow grave, she stops her actions and seems puzzled. But once she realizes what you have done to her, she will have a hard time to decide if she ever wants to escape it. Confronted with her old self, can she still look her lost ones in the eye or is her true self long gone?', CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, -12, 0, 0, 0, 0, -8, 0, 0)
