of pride. For one their splendor sets them apart of the ''lesser'' fae and on the other side it is a great way to contend with others of their kind. Many of their kind are bent on being the best in one regard and all of them strive to have the most beautiful wings or the most enticing appearance. Despite this minor consistency, individual strife and personalities are frequent and a pixie can wear proper garments like a lady, leaflets like other fae, or nothing at all while garnishing their bodies with everything or nothing. However, when engaging a fae, one should always make sure that it isn''t a pixie in disguise, because if there remains a chance, one shouldn''t expect to come out of the adventure the same again, or come out of it at all. For their gift is one to be shared!', NULL, CAST(100.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), N'female', N'full', N'', N'pixie_jbovinne.jpg', 0, CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), CAST(0.00 AS Decimal(18, 2)), 0, 0, 4, 0, -10, 4, 0, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0)
